{
  "texts": [
    "We asked models to infer how many red blocks would fall if the grey block was removed.",
    "For this condition, Zhou and colleagues 100 collected data from 42 participants.",
    "We again report the absolute distance between model predictions and the ground truth for each image (Fig. 3b).",
    "We calculate a random baseline which uses the mean between 0 and the number of blocks for each specific image as the prediction.",
    "We also ask the models for a rating between 0 and 100 for how responsible the grey block is for the stability of the tower."
  ]
}